<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,727,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,835,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is considered widespread in the Caucasian region, the whole of 
<collectingCountry box="[1195,1294,835,861]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1307,1388,835,861]" name="Cyprus" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingRegion box="[191,269,871,897]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Alborz</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[306,351,871,897]" name="Iran" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[365,590,871,897]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref14690" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2002) The species of Perla (Plecoptera: Perlidae): evidence from egg morphology. Scopolia, 49, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">Sivec &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Darilmaz, M. C. &amp; Salur, A. &amp; Muranyi, D. &amp; Vincon, G." box="[601,835,871,898]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref13038" refString="Darilmaz, M. C., Salur, A., Muranyi, D. &amp; Vincon, G. (2016) Contribution to the knowledge of Turkish stoneflies with annotated catalogue (Insecta: Plecoptera). Zootaxa, 4074 (1), 1 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4074.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Darilmaz 
<emphasis box="[712,768,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). This is contrary to 
<bibRefCitation author="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[1064,1389,871,897]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" refId="ref14803" refString="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A. (2009) Key to the stoneflies (Insecta, Plecoptera) of Russia and adjacent countries. Imagines and nymphs (in Russian). Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 382 pp." type="book" year="2009">Teslenko &amp; Zhiltzova (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cherchesova, S. K. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[151,519,907,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" refId="ref12957" refString="Cherchesova, S. K. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A. (2013) Opredelitel vesnyanok (Plecoptera) Kavkaza. RGAU-MI K. A. T, Moskva-Vladikavkaz, 113 pp." type="book" year="2013">Cherchesova &amp; Zhiltzova (2013)</bibRefCitation>
who considered it an endemic of the Greater Caucasus. This difference of opinion is based on the disputed synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Klapalek, 1921" authorityName="Klapalek" authorityYear="1921" box="[583,952,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviata">
<emphasis box="[583,773,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Perla abbreviata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Klapalek, F." box="[780,952,943,969]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="57 - 67" refId="ref13903" refString="Klapalek, F. (1921) Plecopteres nouveaux. I. Sous-famille des Perlinae et Neoperlinae. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 61, 57 - 67." type="journal article" year="1921">Klapálek, 1921</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zwick, 1975" authorityName="Zwick" authorityYear="1975" box="[1007,1270,942,969]" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[1007,1117,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">P. persica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zwick, P." box="[1125,1270,942,969]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="387 - 396" refId="ref15736" refString="Zwick, P. (1975) Weitere Plecoptera aus Anatolien. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 48 (3 - 4), 387 - 396." type="journal article" year="1975">Zwick, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These species were synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" box="[447,589,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis box="[447,589,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">P. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to their similar eggs (
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[897,1130,979,1005]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref14690" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2002) The species of Perla (Plecoptera: Perlidae): evidence from egg morphology. Scopolia, 49, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">Sivec &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
), however, their larvae are distinctly different. Similarly to the above species, our identification is based on larvae that agrees well with the recent description of the larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" box="[528,669,1051,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis box="[528,669,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">P. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Greater Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Cherchesova, S." box="[994,1355,1051,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" pagination="321 - 326" refId="ref15605" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Cherchesova, S. K (2003) Description of the larva of genus Perla Geoff. (Plecoptera, Perlidae) from the Caucasus. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 82 (2), 321 - 326. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2003">Zhiltzova &amp; Cherchesova 2003</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Perla caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a more potamal species than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" box="[614,720,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[614,720,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">P. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[732,855,1087,1113]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
specimens occurred in low and medium-high elevations, mostly in small rivers. These are the first exact locality data from 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1082,1123,1149]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="16" pageNumber="74">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
